14) Runbook (Pasteable Prompt Snippets)
Phase 1 — Prewrite:
“Fill sections 0–1 completely. Challenge weak answers with 3 alternatives each. Select the most commercially compelling.”

Phase 2 — Outline:
“Generate the beat outline (section 2) with word targets and emotional beats. Ensure twist placements hit 20/50/90% ±3%.”

Phase 3 — Draft:
“For Chapter N, use the Scene Forge. Maintain POV integrity. Enforce sensory trio. End with an exit hook.”

Phase 4 — Score & Revise:
“Apply the Scorecard. Any category < 85 triggers a targeted rewrite. Output the delta only.”

Phase 5 — Final Polish:
“Run echo/inversion checks, clue/payoff ledger, and produce back-cover copy + 10 titles. Optimize first page for bookstore test.”
